<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#00ff00">Originally posted by Verant_Hater_II on 05-13-2001 05:08 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Its pretty obvious that the company producing "Dawn" is making a Horizons clone, and that 4 posters here are the developers themselves trying to act like us. Here are my 3 personal rules when making a game:

1. Do not insult your *demographic audiences intelligence.

2. Never insult the company you wish to beat. Just sit back and focus on your work, then they will be the ones trying to beat you.

3. If the product is good, you wont have to push it. The product should be able to push itself.

*demographic: age, preference, likes/dislikes, similarities, etc etc, the crowd of people you aim your product for

Just take Artifact Entertainment into example, I cant think of any instance where they broke any of the rules above. Everyone knows its going to rock our world, so they dont have to go around forums spreading the links and hyping it and such.

For those who dont know about it (may God help you) here is the homepage:

http://www.artifact-entertainment.com/horizons

I think they may have changed it but you shouldnt have trouble finding the IGN Vault page, which is kinda lame. But Horizons definatley takes a big poop all over Dawn even if it isnt Vaporware.

------------------
Your local newbie flamer.</TEXTAREA>
